headline: Morgan Stanley Hires $1.4 Billion Advisor Team From Merrill Lynch
summary: BEST PRACTICES  Morgan Stanley recruited a financial advisor team from Merrill Lynch that previously oversaw more than $1.4 billion in client assets, according to a source familiar with the matter.  The team joined Morgan last week in Bloomfield Hills, Mich.

headline: Morgan Stanley Expects an IPO Surge. This Deal Positions Its Wealth Unit to Profit.
summary: A new partnership with private-company stock tracker Carta will deliver newly wealthy clients to its advisory business, says wealth management head Jed Finn.
